    "id": "ses-171ba711eae0b88e",
    "provider": "claude",
    "agent": "nube-marketing",
    "prompt": "{\"agency\":\"skip\",\"audience\":\"Systems integrators\",\"budget\":\"$10k - $50k\",\"channels\":\"linkedin,email\",\"notes\":\"Focus on AU market\",\"product\":\"Rubix Edge Controller\",\"timeline\":\"1 quarter\"}",
    "result": "# Marketing Plan: Rubix Edge Controller ‚Äî AU Market\n\n**Target Audience:** Systems Integrators (Building Automation / IoT)\n**Budget:** $10k‚Äì$50k | **Timeline:** Q3 2026 (1 Quarter) | **Primary Channels:** LinkedIn, Email\n\n---\n\n## 1. Key Messaging \u0026 Value Propositions\n\n**Core Positioning:**\n\u003e Rubix Edge Controller ‚Äî the open, protocol-agnostic edge platform that lets systems integrators deliver smarter buildings faster, with less vendor lock-in.\n\n**Value Propositions for AU Systems Integrators:**\n\n| Message | Why It Resonates |\n|---|---|\n| **Protocol-agnostic integration** ‚Äî BACnet, Modbus, LoRa, REST APIs from a single device | SIs juggle multiple protocols across retrofit and greenfield jobs; one controller simplifies the stack |\n| **Reduce project delivery time** ‚Äî pre-built drivers and a visual configuration layer cut commissioning hours | Time-on-site is the #1 cost driver for AU integrators; faster commissioning = better margins |\n| **Open platform, no lock-in** ‚Äî Linux-based, API-first architecture lets you own the customer relationship | AU SIs are wary of being locked into a single OEM's ecosystem; openness is a competitive differentiator |\n| **Local-first edge compute** ‚Äî data processing and control logic runs on-prem, even when the cloud is unreachable | Critical for AU sites with unreliable connectivity (regional, industrial, remote campuses) |\n| **Australian-supported** ‚Äî NubeIO is AU-based with local engineering, support, and stock | De-risks procurement and support vs. importing from overseas vendors with timezone mismatches |\n\n**Proof Points to Develop:**\n- 2‚Äì3 AU case studies (e.g. commercial HVAC retrofit, multi-site energy monitoring)\n- Quantified stat: \"X% reduction in commissioning time\" from a real deployment\n- Partner testimonial from an existing AU SI\n\n---\n\n## 2. Channel Strategy\n\n### LinkedIn (Primary ‚Äî ~40% of budget)\n\n| Tactic | Detail | Est. Cost |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Company page content** | 2 posts/week: technical tips, case study snippets, product updates, industry commentary (NABERS, Section J, HVAC trends) | Internal effort |\n| **Sponsored content ads** | Target: AU-based job titles ‚Äî \"Systems Integrator\", \"BMS Engineer\", \"Controls Engineer\", \"Building Automation\", \"HVAC Controls\" at companies with 10‚Äì200 employees | $4k‚Äì$8k/quarter |\n| **LinkedIn Lead Gen Forms** | Gate a technical whitepaper or ROI calculator behind a lead form; lower friction than landing pages | Included in ad spend |\n| **Founder/team thought leadership** | Personal posts from NubeIO leadership on open-source edge, AU building tech trends | Internal effort |\n\n**Content Calendar Themes (rotate weekly):**\n- Week 1: Technical how-to / integration tip\n- Week 2: Customer story or use case\n- Week 3: Industry trend / regulation commentary\n- Week 4: Product feature spotlight\n\n### Email (Primary ‚Äî ~20% of budget)\n\n| Tactic | Detail | Est. Cost |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Lead nurture sequence** | 5-email drip for new leads: (1) Welcome + positioning, (2) Technical overview PDF, (3) Case study, (4) ROI comparison, (5) Book a demo CTA | $1k‚Äì$2k (tooling + copywriting) |\n| **Monthly newsletter** | Curated for SIs: product updates, integration guides, AU industry news | Internal effort |\n| **Re-engagement campaign** | Target cold leads / past enquiries with a \"what's new\" angle | Internal effort |\n| **Tooling** | Email platform (Mailchimp/Brevo free-tier may suffice at early volumes) | $0‚Äì$500/quarter |\n\n### Content Assets (Supporting ‚Äî ~30% of budget)\n\n| Asset | Purpose | Est. Cost |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Technical whitepaper** ‚Äî \"The SI's Guide to Open Edge Controllers\" | Lead magnet for LinkedIn + email | $2k‚Äì$4k (freelance writer + internal review) |\n| **ROI calculator** (spreadsheet or simple web tool) | Lets SIs estimate commissioning time savings | $1k‚Äì$3k |\n| **2 √ó customer case studies** (1-pager each) | Social proof for mid-funnel leads | $1k‚Äì$2k |\n| **Product comparison sheet** ‚Äî Rubix vs. Tridium/Honeywell/Schneider | Arms SIs with switching justification | Internal effort |\n| **Short demo video** (2‚Äì3 min, screen capture + voiceover) | LinkedIn + email embed, landing page | $1k‚Äì$2k |\n\n### Events (Supplementary ‚Äî ~10% of budget)\n\n| Tactic | Detail | Est. Cost |\n|---|---|---|\n| **1 √ó webinar** ‚Äî \"Open Edge for SIs: Live Demo + Q\u0026A\" | Lead gen + pipeline acceleration; promote via LinkedIn + email | $500‚Äì$1k (platform + promotion) |\n| **ARBS 2026 / BuildingIQ meetup attendance** | If timing aligns ‚Äî networking, not a booth. Meet SIs face-to-face | $1k‚Äì$2k (travel + collateral) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Timeline \u0026 Milestones\n\n### Month 1 ‚Äî Foundation\n\n- [ ] Finalise messaging framework and SI persona\n- [ ] Set up LinkedIn ad account, audiences, tracking (UTMs, LinkedIn Insight Tag)\n- [ ] Set up email platform + lead nurture sequence (5 emails)\n- [ ] Commission whitepaper and begin case study interviews\n- [ ] Launch LinkedIn organic posting cadence (2x/week)\n- [ ] **Milestone:** First LinkedIn ad campaign live by end of Month 1\n\n### Month 2 ‚Äî Acceleration\n\n- [ ] Publish whitepaper; launch as gated lead magnet on LinkedIn Lead Gen Forms\n- [ ] Publish first case study; distribute via email + LinkedIn\n- [ ] Launch monthly newsletter (first edition)\n- [ ] Record and publish demo video\n- [ ] Host webinar ‚Äî promote 2 weeks in advance\n- [ ] **Milestone:** 50+ marketing-qualified leads (MQLs) captured\n\n### Month 3 ‚Äî Optimisation \u0026 Pipeline\n\n- [ ] Publish second case study + comparison sheet\n- [ ] Optimise LinkedIn ads based on Month 1‚Äì2 data (pause underperformers, scale winners)\n- [ ] Run email re-engagement campaign to cold leads\n- [ ] Deliver ROI calculator asset\n- [ ] Attend 1 industry event / meetup if available\n- [ ] **Milestone:** 20+ demo requests or sales conversations from marketing-sourced leads\n\n---\n\n## 4. Success Metrics \u0026 KPIs\n\n| Metric | Target (end of quarter) | How to Measure |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Marketing Qualified Leads (MQLs)** | 100‚Äì150 | CRM / email platform |\n| **Demo requests / sales conversations** | 20‚Äì30 | CRM pipeline stage |\n| **LinkedIn ad CTR** | \u003e0.8% | LinkedIn Campaign Manager |\n| **Cost per lead (CPL)** | \u003c$50 | Ad spend √∑ leads |\n| **Email open rate** | \u003e30% | Email platform |\n| **Email click-through rate** | \u003e4% | Email platform |\n| **Whitepaper downloads** | 50+ | Landing page / Lead Gen Forms |\n| **Webinar registrations** | 40+ (25+ attendees) | Webinar platform |\n| **Pipeline value generated** | $100k+ (attributed to marketing) | CRM |\n\n---\n\n## Budget Summary\n\n| Category | Low Estimate | High Estimate |\n|---|---|---|\n| LinkedIn ads | $4,000 | $8,000 |\n| Content creation (whitepaper, case studies, video) | $5,000 | $11,000 |\n| Email tooling + copywriting | $1,000 | $2,500 |\n| Webinar + events | $1,500 | $3,000 |\n| **Total** | **$11,500** | **$24,500** |\n\nThis leaves headroom within the $50k cap for scaling LinkedIn ads if early results are strong, or for a second webinar / additional content assets in Month 3.\n\n---\n\n**Next steps:** If you'd like, I can drill deeper into any section ‚Äî LinkedIn ad copy drafts, the email nurture sequence, or the whitepaper outline.",
