    "provider": "claude",
    "agent": "nube-marketing",
    "prompt": "{\"audience\":\"new controller\",\"budget\":\"\\u003c $10k\",\"channels\":\"linkedin\",\"notes\":\"all\",\"product\":\"new controller\",\"timeline\":\"1 month\"}",
    "result": "\n\nI'll use the marketing plan tool to generate this for you.# Marketing Plan: NubeIO New Controller\n\n**Budget:** \u003c $10,000 | **Timeline:** 1 Month | **Primary Channel:** LinkedIn\n\n---\n\n## 1. Key Messaging \u0026 Value Propositions\n\n**Core Message:**\n\u003e \"The new NubeIO controller ‚Äî smarter edge computing for modern buildings, at a fraction of the cost.\"\n\n**Value Propositions:**\n\n| Pillar | Message | Proof Point |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| **Cost Efficiency** | Reduce hardware costs without sacrificing capability | Competitive pricing vs. legacy BMS controllers |\n| **Open Protocol** | Works with BACnet, Modbus, LoRa ‚Äî no vendor lock-in | Protocol support list, integration case studies |\n| **Edge Intelligence** | Process data at the edge, act in real-time | On-device logic, local decision-making without cloud dependency |\n| **Easy Deployment** | Commission in minutes, not days | Web-based configuration, zero-touch provisioning |\n| **Scalability** | Start with one controller, scale to an entire portfolio | Fleet management via Rubix platform |\n\n**Buyer Personas:**\n\n- **Facility Managers** ‚Äî want reliability, simplicity, lower operating costs\n- **System Integrators** ‚Äî want open protocols, fast commissioning, margin\n- **Building Owners / Property Managers** ‚Äî want ROI, energy savings, tenant comfort\n\n---\n\n## 2. Channel Strategy (LinkedIn-Focused)\n\n### LinkedIn (Primary ‚Äî 60% of budget = ~$6,000)\n\n| Tactic | Details | Budget |\n|--------|---------|--------|\n| **Sponsored Posts** (2x/week) | Product features, use cases, comparison graphics | $3,000 |\n| **LinkedIn Articles** (2 long-form) | \"Why Open Controllers Matter in 2026\", \"Edge vs. Cloud in Building Automation\" | $500 (design/editing) |\n| **Targeted InMail Campaign** | Direct outreach to facility managers \u0026 integrators in AU/US/UK | $1,500 |\n| **Video Content** (2 short demos) | Unboxing + commissioning walkthrough, protocol integration demo | $1,000 |\n\n**Targeting Criteria:**\n- Job titles: Facility Manager, Building Engineer, Controls Engineer, System Integrator, Energy Manager\n- Industries: Commercial Real Estate, Property Management, HVAC, Building Automation\n- Company size: 50‚Äì5,000 employees\n- Regions: Australia, US, UK, SE Asia\n\n### Content (20% of budget = ~$2,000)\n\n| Asset | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| **Product One-Pager (PDF)** | Downloadable spec sheet for lead capture |\n| **Landing Page** | Dedicated page with CTA ‚Üí request demo / get pricing |\n| **Blog Post** | SEO-optimized \"Introducing the New NubeIO Controller\" |\n| **Comparison Infographic** | New controller vs. legacy BMS controllers |\n\n### Email (10% of budget = ~$500)\n\n| Email | Timing | Audience |\n|-------|--------|----------|\n| **Announcement** | Week 1 | Existing contacts \u0026 newsletter list |\n| **Feature Deep-Dive** | Week 2 | Engaged openers from email 1 |\n| **Case Study / Social Proof** | Week 3 | Full list |\n| **Limited-Time Offer / CTA** | Week 4 | Engaged leads |\n\n### Events / Community (10% of budget = ~$500)\n\n| Tactic | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **LinkedIn Live / Webinar** | 30-min live demo, Q\u0026A with engineering team (Week 3) |\n| **Partner Co-Promotion** | Cross-post with distributor / integrator partners |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Timeline \u0026 Milestones\n\n| Week | Focus | Key Deliverables |\n|------|-------|-----------------|\n| **Week 1** (Apr 15‚Äì21) | **Prep \u0026 Soft Launch** | Landing page live, product one-pager done, announcement email sent, first 2 LinkedIn posts published |\n| **Week 2** (Apr 22‚Äì28) | **Awareness Push** | LinkedIn ad campaigns live, InMail outreach begins, blog post published, comparison infographic shared |\n| **Week 3** (Apr 29‚ÄìMay 5) | **Engagement \u0026 Demo** | LinkedIn Live / webinar hosted, video demos published, feature deep-dive email sent, retargeting ads active |\n| **Week 4** (May 6‚Äì12) | **Conversion \u0026 Wrap-Up** | CTA/offer email sent, lead follow-ups, campaign performance review, report \u0026 next-steps doc delivered |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Success Metrics \u0026 KPIs\n\n| Metric | Target | How to Measure |\n|--------|--------|----------------|\n| **LinkedIn Impressions** | 50,000+ | LinkedIn Campaign Manager |\n| **LinkedIn Engagement Rate** | \u003e 2.5% | Likes, comments, shares / impressions |\n| **Landing Page Visits** | 500+ | Google Analytics / UTM tracking |\n| **Leads Generated** (form fills / demo requests) | 30+ | CRM / landing page form |\n| **Email Open Rate** | \u003e 25% | Email platform (Mailchimp, HubSpot, etc.) |\n| **Email Click-Through Rate** | \u003e 4% | Email platform |\n| **Webinar Registrations** | 50+ | Registration form |\n| **Webinar Attendees** | 25+ | Live attendance count |\n| **Sales Conversations Started** | 10+ | CRM / sales team tracking |\n| **Cost Per Lead** | \u003c $200 | Total spend / leads generated |\n\n---\n\n## Budget Summary\n\n| Category | Allocation |\n|----------|-----------|\n| LinkedIn Ads \u0026 InMail | $6,000 |\n| Content Creation (design, copy, video) | $2,000 |\n| Email Marketing | $500 |\n| Webinar / Events | $500 |\n| **Total** | **$9,000** |\n| **Contingency** | **$1,000** |\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. **This week:** Finalize product messaging and create landing page\n2. **Assign owners:** Who handles content creation, ad management, email sends?\n3. **Set up tracking:** UTM parameters, LinkedIn Insight Tag, CRM pipeline stage for \"New Controller\" leads\n4. **Brief sales team:** Ensure they know the messaging and have the one-pager ready for follow-ups\n\nWant me to dive deeper into any section, generate specific LinkedIn post copy, or create the landing page content?",
    "status": "done",
    "duration_ms": 45329,
    "cost_usd": 0.10839549999999998,
    "user_id": "usr-2d1a32a2a3c9c373",
