    "prompt": "what can you do?",
    "result": "Here's what I can help you with:\n\n## General Software Engineering\n- **Read, write, and edit code** across your codebase\n- **Debug issues** ‚Äî trace bugs, read errors, and fix them\n- **Refactor code** ‚Äî restructure, rename, simplify\n- **Explain code** ‚Äî walk through logic, architecture, patterns\n- **Run commands** ‚Äî build, test, lint, deploy via the terminal\n- **Git operations** ‚Äî commits, branches, diffs, PRs\n- **Search** ‚Äî find files, grep for symbols, explore the codebase\n\n## Your Project-Specific MCP Tools\nYou have a `nube` MCP server with tools for:\n\n- **Rubix Developer** ‚Äî manage devices (create, list, get, update, restart), read device points, write points, check health, get summaries\n- **Nube Marketing** ‚Äî generate marketing plans, content reviews (including QA variants)\n- **Nube Admin** ‚Äî create skill QA\n- **Info** ‚Äî get system info\n\n## Other Capabilities\n- **Web search \u0026 fetch** ‚Äî look things up online\n- **PR reviews** ‚Äî review pull requests for quality/security\n- **Security reviews** ‚Äî audit pending changes for vulnerabilities\n- **Scheduling** ‚Äî set up recurring tasks or cron-based agents\n- **Google integrations** ‚Äî Gmail, Calendar, Drive (via authentication)\n- **Jupyter notebooks** ‚Äî read and edit `.ipynb` files\n- **Plan \u0026 architect** ‚Äî design implementation strategies before coding\n\n## Skills (slash commands)\n`/commit`, `/review`, `/security-review`, `/init`, `/simplify`, `/claude-api`, and more.\n\nWhat would you like to work on?",
