    "prompt": "{\"agency\":\"skip\",\"audience\":\"Systems integrators\",\"budget\":\"$10k - $50k\",\"channels\":\"linkedin,email\",\"notes\":\"Focus on AU market\",\"product\":\"Rubix Edge Controller\",\"timeline\":\"1 quarter\"}",
    "result": "# Marketing Plan: Rubix Edge Controller ‚Äî AU Market\n\n**Target Audience:** Systems Integrators (Building Automation / IoT)\n**Budget:** $10k ‚Äì $50k | **Timeline:** Q3 2026 (1 quarter) | **Primary Channels:** LinkedIn, Email\n\n---\n\n## 1. Key Messaging \u0026 Value Propositions\n\n### Core Positioning\n\u003e *Rubix Edge Controller: The open, programmable edge platform that lets systems integrators deliver smarter buildings ‚Äî faster.*\n\n### Value Propositions (ranked by SI priority)\n\n| # | Message | Why It Resonates with SIs |\n|---|---------|--------------------------|\n| 1 | **Protocol-agnostic integration** ‚Äî BACnet, Modbus, LoRa, and more from a single controller | SIs juggle multi-vendor sites; one box reduces truck rolls and spares inventory |\n| 2 | **Open \u0026 programmable** ‚Äî no vendor lock-in, extensible with custom logic and apps | SIs protect margins by owning the software layer, not renting it |\n| 3 | **Remote-first management** ‚Äî deploy, configure, and troubleshoot from anywhere via Rubix Cloud | AU geography means sites are spread across vast distances; remote access cuts travel costs |\n| 4 | **Lower project cost** ‚Äî competitive hardware + no per-point licensing | Helps SIs win tenders on price without sacrificing capability |\n| 5 | **AU-based support \u0026 stock** ‚Äî local engineering team, local warehouse | De-risks supply chain vs. importing from overseas with long lead times |\n\n### Proof Points to Develop\n- 1‚Äì2 AU case studies (target: commercial HVAC retrofit, multi-site retail/facility)\n- TCO comparison vs. incumbent controllers (Tridium/Niagara, Schneider, Honeywell)\n- Live demo or sandbox environment SIs can access themselves\n\n---\n\n## 2. Channel Strategy\n\n### LinkedIn (Primary ‚Äî ~40% of effort)\n\n| Tactic | Detail | Cadence |\n|--------|--------|---------|\n| **Company page content** | Technical posts, mini case studies, product tips, industry commentary | 3√ó/week |\n| **Sponsored content ads** | Targeted at AU-based SIs, BMS engineers, facility managers | Ongoing, A/B tested fortnightly |\n| **LinkedIn Lead Gen Forms** | Gated asset (e.g. \"SI Guide to Open Edge Controllers\") driving email capture | 1 campaign/month |\n| **Personal thought leadership** | Nube founders/engineers posting insights, tagging AU SI community | 2√ó/week |\n| **LinkedIn Groups \u0026 comments** | Engage in ASHRAE AU, BACnet Interest Group, Smart Buildings AU groups | Daily |\n\n**Targeting criteria:** Australia, job titles containing *systems integrator, BMS engineer, controls engineer, building automation, HVAC controls, project engineer*; companies in mechanical/electrical contracting, BMS, and energy services.\n\n**Budget allocation:** $3k‚Äì$8k/month on LinkedIn Ads (sponsored content + lead gen forms)\n\n### Email (Primary ‚Äî ~35% of effort)\n\n| Tactic | Detail | Cadence |\n|--------|--------|---------|\n| **Nurture sequence** | 5-email drip for new leads: intro ‚Üí pain points ‚Üí case study ‚Üí demo invite ‚Üí offer | Triggered on signup |\n| **Monthly newsletter** | Product updates, AU project highlights, technical tips, upcoming events | Monthly |\n| **Targeted outreach** | Personalised 1:1 emails to top 50 AU SI firms (research-backed, not spam) | Weeks 1‚Äì4, then follow-ups |\n| **Event follow-up** | Post-webinar/post-event sequences | As needed |\n\n**Tooling:** Use an email platform (e.g. Mailchimp, HubSpot Starter) with CRM integration. Budget: $500‚Äì$1k/quarter for tooling.\n\n**List building:**\n- LinkedIn Lead Gen Form captures\n- Website form (gated content downloads)\n- Purchased/rented list of AU mechanical contractors and BMS firms (use cautiously, comply with AU Spam Act 2003)\n- Manual research of top 100 AU SI firms from AMCA, AIRAH, and BACnet AU member directories\n\n### Supporting Channels (~25% of effort)\n\n| Channel | Tactic | Budget |\n|---------|--------|--------|\n| **Webinars** | 1 live technical webinar per month (e.g. \"Migrating Legacy BMS to Open Edge\") | $500/webinar (promotion) |\n| **Content/SEO** | 2 blog posts/month on nube-io.com targeting AU SI search terms | Internal effort |\n| **Industry events** | Attend 1‚Äì2 AU trade events (ARBS, Total Facilities, AIRAH events) as visitor or small exhibitor | $2k‚Äì$5k if exhibiting |\n| **Partner co-marketing** | Joint content with AU distributors or complementary vendors (sensors, cloud platforms) | In-kind |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Timeline \u0026 Milestones (Q3 2026)\n\n### Month 1 ‚Äî Foundation (Weeks 1‚Äì4)\n\n- [ ] Finalise messaging framework and 1-page SI sales sheet (PDF)\n- [ ] Publish gated asset: *\"The SI's Guide to Open Edge Controllers\"*\n- [ ] Set up LinkedIn ad campaigns (2 audiences, 2 creatives each)\n- [ ] Build email nurture sequence (5 emails)\n- [ ] Research and compile target list of top 100 AU SI firms\n- [ ] Launch personalised outreach to first 25 firms\n- [ ] Publish 2 blog posts + 6 LinkedIn organic posts\n- **Milestone:** Ad campaigns live, nurture sequence active, first leads captured\n\n### Month 2 ‚Äî Acceleration (Weeks 5‚Äì8)\n\n- [ ] Host first live webinar (*\"Open Edge for Multi-Site BMS\"*)\n- [ ] Launch second LinkedIn Lead Gen campaign with new gated asset (TCO calculator or comparison guide)\n- [ ] Outreach to next 25 SI firms\n- [ ] Publish 1 AU case study (even if brief/anonymised)\n- [ ] Send first monthly newsletter\n- [ ] Optimise LinkedIn ads based on Month 1 data (pause underperformers, scale winners)\n- **Milestone:** 50+ marketing-qualified leads (MQLs), first demo requests from inbound\n\n### Month 3 ‚Äî Conversion \u0026 Review (Weeks 9‚Äì13)\n\n- [ ] Host second webinar (*\"Live Demo: Rubix Edge in a Retrofit Project\"*)\n- [ ] Complete outreach to remaining 50 SI firms\n- [ ] Retarget engaged-but-not-converted leads via LinkedIn + email\n- [ ] Attend 1 industry event (if timing aligns) or host a small in-person SI roundtable in Sydney/Melbourne\n- [ ] Publish second case study\n- [ ] Quarter-end performance review and planning for Q4\n- **Milestone:** Pipeline value identified, first SI partner agreements or POC commitments\n\n---\n\n## 4. Success Metrics \u0026 KPIs\n\n| Category | KPI | Q3 Target |\n|----------|-----|-----------|\n| **Awareness** | LinkedIn impressions | 100,000+ |\n| **Awareness** | Website visits from AU | 1,500+ unique visitors |\n| **Lead Gen** | Marketing-qualified leads (MQLs) | 75‚Äì150 |\n| **Lead Gen** | Email list size (AU SIs) | 300+ |\n| **Engagement** | LinkedIn engagement rate | \u003e2% |\n| **Engagement** | Email open rate | \u003e30% |\n| **Engagement** | Email click-through rate | \u003e5% |\n| **Engagement** | Webinar attendees | 25+ per session |\n| **Pipeline** | Demo requests / POC conversations | 15‚Äì25 |\n| **Pipeline** | Qualified sales opportunities | 5‚Äì10 |\n| **Revenue** | SI partner agreements or first orders | 2‚Äì3 |\n\n### Tracking \u0026 Reporting\n- **Weekly:** LinkedIn ad performance, email campaign metrics\n- **Fortnightly:** Lead quality review with sales (MQL ‚Üí SQL conversion)\n- **Monthly:** Full dashboard review, budget reconciliation, content calendar update\n- **End of quarter:** ROI analysis, cost-per-lead, pipeline attribution report\n\n---\n\n## Budget Breakdown (Indicative)\n\n| Line Item | Low ($10k) | Mid ($30k) | High ($50k) |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| LinkedIn Ads | $5,000 | $15,000 | $24,000 |\n| Email tooling | $500 | $1,000 | $1,500 |\n| Content creation (design, copywriting) | $2,000 | $5,000 | $8,000 |\n| Webinar platform + promotion | $1,000 | $2,000 | $3,000 |\n| Event attendance/exhibiting | $0 | $4,000 | $8,000 |\n| Target list / data enrichment | $500 | $1,000 | $2,000 |\n| Contingency | $1,000 | $2,000 | $3,500 |\n| **Total** | **$10,000** | **$30,000** | **$50,000** |\n\n---\n\n## Key Risks \u0026 Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|\n| Low brand awareness in AU SI market | Lead with technical credibility ‚Äî engineering-led content, not marketing fluff |\n| SIs are conservative / loyal to incumbents | Focus on *complement, then replace* messaging; offer risk-free POC |\n| Small addressable audience on LinkedIn | Tight targeting + frequency capping to avoid ad fatigue; rotate creatives fortnightly |\n| Spam Act compliance (email) | Only email opted-in contacts or use legitimate business exception; include unsubscribe in every email |\n\n---\n\nThis plan is designed to be executable by a small team (1‚Äì2 people + occasional contractor support for design/copy). The LinkedIn + email focus keeps things lean while directly reaching the people who specify and install controllers on AU job sites.",
