    "id": "ses-072d1feb3e3fd7cb",
    "provider": "claude",
    "agent": "nube-marketing",
    "prompt": "{\"audience\":\"new controller\",\"budget\":\"\\u003c $10k\",\"channels\":\"linkedin,email\",\"notes\":\"na\",\"product\":\"new controller\",\"timeline\":\"1 month\"}",
    "result": "I'll use the Nube marketing plan tool to generate this for you.Here's a practical, actionable marketing plan for the **New Controller** launch:\n\n---\n\n# Marketing Plan: NubeIO New Controller\n\n**Budget:** \u003c $10k | **Timeline:** 1 month | **Primary Channels:** LinkedIn, Email\n\n---\n\n## 1. Key Messaging \u0026 Value Propositions\n\n**Core Message:**\n\u003e \"Smarter building control, simplified. The new NubeIO controller delivers edge intelligence for modern building automation ‚Äî without the complexity or cost of legacy systems.\"\n\n**Value Propositions:**\n\n| Pillar | Message | Proof Point |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Simplicity** | Deploy in minutes, not days | Plug-and-play setup, web-based configuration |\n| **Edge Intelligence** | Process data locally, act instantly | On-device logic, reduced cloud dependency |\n| **Open \u0026 Interoperable** | Works with your existing systems | BACnet, Modbus, MQTT, REST API support |\n| **Cost Efficiency** | Enterprise capability at SMB pricing | Lower hardware cost + reduced integration labor |\n| **Scalability** | Start with one, scale to thousands | Fleet management via Rubix platform |\n\n**Positioning Statement:**\nFor facility managers, system integrators, and building automation engineers who need reliable, cost-effective edge control ‚Äî the NubeIO controller is the open, programmable alternative to locked-down legacy hardware.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Channel Strategy\n\n### LinkedIn (Primary ‚Äî ~40% of effort)\n\n| Tactic | Details | Budget |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Organic posts** | 3x/week: product teasers, use cases, behind-the-scenes, customer pain points | $0 |\n| **LinkedIn Ads** | Sponsored posts targeting job titles: BMS Engineer, Facility Manager, Controls Engineer, IoT Product Manager | $2,500 |\n| **LinkedIn Articles** | 2 long-form pieces: \"Why Edge Controllers Matter in 2026\" + product deep-dive | $0 |\n| **Employee advocacy** | Team members share and comment on posts | $0 |\n\n**Targeting:** Industries: commercial real estate, HVAC, smart buildings, energy management. Geo: AU, US, UK. Company size: 50‚Äì5,000.\n\n### Email (Primary ‚Äî ~30% of effort)\n\n| Sequence | Timing | Content |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Teaser** | Week 1 | \"Something new is coming\" ‚Äî problem-focused, no product reveal |\n| **Launch announcement** | Week 2 | Product reveal, key specs, hero image, CTA to landing page |\n| **Technical deep-dive** | Week 3 | Architecture, protocols, integration guide, CTA to demo |\n| **Social proof / Case study** | Week 4 | Early adopter results or use-case scenario, CTA to order |\n\n**List segments:** Existing customers, trial users, integrator partners, inbound leads.\n**Budget:** Email platform costs ~$0 (existing tooling assumed), copywriting/design ~$1,000.\n\n### Content (Supporting ‚Äî ~20% of effort)\n\n| Asset | Purpose | Budget |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Landing page** | Central hub ‚Äî specs, benefits, demo CTA | $500 (design) |\n| **Product one-pager (PDF)** | Sales enablement, email attachment | $300 |\n| **2-min product video** | LinkedIn, landing page, email embed | $2,000 |\n| **Blog post** | SEO + organic traffic: \"Introducing the New Controller\" | $0 |\n| **Comparison table** | vs. legacy controllers (Tridium, Distech, etc.) | $0 |\n\n### Events (Lightweight ‚Äî ~10% of effort)\n\n| Tactic | Details | Budget |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Live LinkedIn webinar** | 30-min demo + Q\u0026A, Week 3 | $0 |\n| **Partner demo sessions** | 1:1 virtual demos for top integrator partners | $0 |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Timeline \u0026 Milestones\n\n```\nWEEK 1 ‚Äî PRE-LAUNCH\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Finalize messaging, landing page, one-pager\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Send teaser email to segmented lists\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Begin LinkedIn teaser posts (3x)\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Product video in production\n\nWEEK 2 ‚Äî LAUNCH\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Publish landing page + blog post\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Send launch announcement email\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ LinkedIn launch post (boosted) + ad campaign starts\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Share product video\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Announce webinar date\n\nWEEK 3 ‚Äî EDUCATE\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Send technical deep-dive email\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Host live webinar / demo\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ LinkedIn: post webinar clips, technical content\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Begin partner demo outreach\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Publish comparison table\n\nWEEK 4 ‚Äî CONVERT\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Send social proof / case study email\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ LinkedIn retargeting ads to landing page visitors\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Sales follow-up on webinar attendees + email clickers\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Collect feedback, iterate messaging\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Report on KPIs\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Success Metrics \u0026 KPIs\n\n| Metric | Target | How to Measure |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Landing page visits** | 500+ unique visits | Analytics |\n| **Email open rate** | \u003e 30% | Email platform |\n| **Email click-through rate** | \u003e 5% | Email platform |\n| **LinkedIn post impressions** | 10,000+ total | LinkedIn analytics |\n| **LinkedIn ad CTR** | \u003e 0.8% | LinkedIn Campaign Manager |\n| **Webinar registrations** | 50+ | Registration form |\n| **Webinar attendees** | 25+ | Webinar platform |\n| **Demo requests** | 15+ | Landing page form |\n| **Sales-qualified leads** | 10+ | CRM |\n| **Units ordered (or pipeline created)** | 5+ orders / $50k pipeline | CRM |\n\n---\n\n## Budget Summary\n\n| Item | Cost |\n|---|---|\n| LinkedIn Ads | $2,500 |\n| Product Video | $2,000 |\n| Email Copy \u0026 Design | $1,000 |\n| Landing Page Design | $500 |\n| Product One-Pager | $300 |\n| Contingency / Tools | $700 |\n| **Total** | **$7,000** |\n\n---\n\n## Quick-Start Checklist\n\n- [ ] Lock in product specs and hero image from engineering\n- [ ] Draft landing page copy and wireframe\n- [ ] Segment email lists (customers, partners, leads)\n- [ ] Set up LinkedIn Campaign Manager and audience targeting\n- [ ] Brief video production (even a polished screen recording works at this budget)\n- [ ] Write email sequence (4 emails)\n- [ ] Schedule LinkedIn content calendar (12 posts over 4 weeks)\n- [ ] Set up tracking: UTM parameters, landing page analytics, CRM tagging\n\n---\n\nThis plan keeps spend under $7k, focuses effort on the two highest-ROI channels for B2B IoT (LinkedIn + email), and drives toward measurable pipeline within 30 days. Want me to drill deeper into any section ‚Äî ad copy, email drafts, or the landing page structure?",
