    "id": "ses-4db59641b6023335",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. Generate a tool for a shopping list app.\n\nWhen generating a tool, output a JSON code block with this exact format:\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {},\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { ... }\"\n}\n```\n\nThe JS runtime has: config.get(key), log.info(msg).\n\nCreate a \"check_off_item\" tool that marks a shopping list item as checked/bought. It should take an item name param and toggle its checked status. Keep the script short.",
    "result": "\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"check_off_item\",\n  \"description\": \"Toggle the checked/bought status of a shopping list item\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-write\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"item_name\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"Name of the shopping list item to check off or uncheck\",\n      \"required\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { var list = JSON.parse(config.get('shopping_list') || '[]'); var found = false; for (var i = 0; i \u003c list.length; i++) { if (list[i].name.toLowerCase() === params.item_name.toLowerCase()) { list[i].checked = !list[i].checked; log.info((list[i].checked ? 'Checked' : 'Unchecked') + ': ' + list[i].name); found = true; break; } } if (!found) { log.info('Item not found: ' + params.item_name); return { success: false, error: 'Item not found' }; } config.set('shopping_list', JSON.stringify(list)); return { success: true, item: list.find(function(i) { return i.name.toLowerCase() === params.item_name.toLowerCase(); }) }; }\"\n}\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n\n- Takes an `item_name` parameter (string, required)\n- Reads the shopping list from `config.get('shopping_list')`\n- Finds the item by case-insensitive name match\n- Toggles its `checked` boolean (`true` ‚Üí `false`, `false` ‚Üí `true`)\n- Persists the updated list back via `config.set`\n- Returns the updated item on success, or an error if the item wasn't found\n- Set to `read-write` since it modifies state",
    "status": "done",
    "duration_ms": 8670,
    "cost_usd": 0.05468725,
    "user_id": "usr-2d1a32a2a3c9c373",
    "created_at": "2026-04-15T13:24:45.69579769Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "ses-34c351d9ef1de6af",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. The user is building a store app and needs help creating tools and prompts.\n\nWhen generating a tool, output a JSON code block with this exact format:\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n  \"description\": \"What the tool does\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"param_name\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"Param description\" }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  // Tool logic here\\n  const result = http.get('https://example.com/api');\\n  return { data: result };\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\nWhen generating a prompt, output a JSON code block with this format:\n```json:prompt\n{\n  \"name\": \"prompt_name\",\n  \"description\": \"What the prompt does\",\n  \"body\": \"Markdown template body with {{variable}} placeholders\"\n}\n```\n\nThe JS runtime has these APIs available:\n- http.get(url), http.post(url, body), http.put(url, body), http.patch(url, body), http.delete(url)\n- secrets.get(key) ‚Äî get a secret from the user's app install settings\n- config.get(key) ‚Äî get a non-secret setting\n- log.info(msg), log.warn(msg), log.error(msg)\n- files.read(relativePath) ‚Äî read a file relative to the app directory\n\nHTTP calls are restricted to the app's allowedHosts list. The handle(params) function receives the tool's declared params.\n\nKeep tool scripts concise. Ask clarifying questions if the user's request is ambiguous. Always explain what the generated tool/prompt does.\n\nThe user's app context:\nApp name: \"test\", Description: \"\"\n\nUser request: Create a tool that checks if a URL is reachable",
    "result": "Here's a tool that checks if a URL is reachable by making an HTTP GET request to it:\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"check_url\",\n  \"description\": \"Checks if a URL is reachable by sending an HTTP GET request and returning the status\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to check (e.g. https://example.com)\" }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  try {\\n    const resp = http.get(params.url);\\n    return {\\n      reachable: true,\\n      url: params.url,\\n      status: resp.status\\n    };\\n  } catch (e) {\\n    return {\\n      reachable: false,\\n      url: params.url,\\n      error: e.message\\n    };\\n  }\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n- Takes a `url` parameter and sends an HTTP GET request to it\n- Returns `reachable: true` with the HTTP status code on success\n- Returns `reachable: false` with the error message if the request fails (DNS failure, timeout, connection refused, etc.)\n\n**Note:** The URL's host must be listed in your app's `allowedHosts` configuration, otherwise the HTTP call will be blocked by the runtime sandbox.",
    "status": "done",
    "duration_ms": 8489,
    "cost_usd": 0.057033,
    "user_id": "usr-2d1a32a2a3c9c373",
    "created_at": "2026-04-15T13:41:26.462057915Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "ses-10d1b99f49b1a71f",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. The user is building a store app and needs help creating tools and prompts.\n\nWhen generating a tool, output a JSON code block with this exact format:\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n  \"description\": \"What the tool does\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"param_name\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"Param description\" }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  // Tool logic here\\n  const result = http.get('https://example.com/api');\\n  return { data: result };\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\nWhen generating a prompt, output a JSON code block with this format:\n```json:prompt\n{\n  \"name\": \"prompt_name\",\n  \"description\": \"What the prompt does\",\n  \"body\": \"Markdown template body with {{variable}} placeholders\"\n}\n```\n\nThe JS runtime has these APIs available:\n- http.get(url), http.post(url, body), http.put(url, body), http.patch(url, body), http.delete(url)\n- secrets.get(key) ‚Äî get a secret from the user's app install settings\n- config.get(key) ‚Äî get a non-secret setting\n- log.info(msg), log.warn(msg), log.error(msg)\n- files.read(relativePath) ‚Äî read a file relative to the app directory\n\nHTTP calls are restricted to the app's allowedHosts list. The handle(params) function receives the tool's declared params.\n\nKeep tool scripts concise. Ask clarifying questions if the user's request is ambiguous. Always explain what the generated tool/prompt does.\n\nThe user's app context:\nApp name: \"test\", Description: \"\"\n\nUser request: Create a tool that checks if a URL is reachable",
    "result": "\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"check_url\",\n  \"description\": \"Checks if a URL is reachable by making an HTTP GET request and returning the status\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to check\" }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  try {\\n    const resp = http.get(params.url);\\n    return { reachable: true, status: resp.status };\\n  } catch (e) {\\n    return { reachable: false, error: e.message };\\n  }\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\nThis tool takes a `url` parameter, makes a GET request to it, and returns:\n\n- **reachable: true** + the HTTP status code if the request succeeds\n- **reachable: false** + the error message if the request fails\n\nNote: The target domain must be included in your app's `allowedHosts` list for the HTTP call to work.",
