  {
    "id": "ses-997f5ba3ae8b7da2",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. The user will describe an app they want. Generate a structured plan as a single JSON code block.\n\nIMPORTANT: Respond with ONLY a ```json code block, no other text before or after it.\n\nThe JSON must have this exact structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"app-slug-name\",\n  \"displayName\": \"Human Readable Name\",\n  \"description\": \"A clear description of what this app does (at least 20 characters)\",\n  \"category\": \"utilities\",\n  \"tools\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n      \"description\": \"What this tool does\",\n      \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"param_name\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"What this param is\" }\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"prompts\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt_name\",\n      \"description\": \"What this prompt does\",\n      \"arguments\": [\n        { \"name\": \"arg_name\", \"description\": \"What this arg is\", \"required\": true }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nCategories: iot-devices, analytics, devops, marketing, design, utilities, integrations, automation.\nTool classes: read-only, read-write, destructive.\nGenerate 2-5 tools and 0-2 prompts. Keep names lowercase with underscores.\nThe \"name\" field should be a lowercase slug with hyphens.\n\nUser's app idea:\nA URL health checker that monitors uptime of websites",
    "result": "\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"url-health-checker\",\n  \"displayName\": \"URL Health Checker\",\n  \"description\": \"Monitors the uptime and response health of websites by performing periodic checks, tracking status codes, response times, and availability history.\",\n  \"category\": \"utilities\",\n  \"tools\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"check_url\",\n      \"description\": \"Performs a single health check on a given URL and returns status code, response time, and availability status\",\n      \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The full URL to check (e.g. https://example.com)\" },\n        \"timeout_seconds\": { \"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Request timeout in seconds (default: 10)\" }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"add_monitor\",\n      \"description\": \"Adds a URL to the monitoring watchlist with a specified check interval\",\n      \"toolClass\": \"read-write\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to monitor\" },\n        \"label\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"A friendly label for this monitor\" },\n        \"interval_minutes\": { \"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"How often to check in minutes (default: 5)\" }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"remove_monitor\",\n      \"description\": \"Removes a URL from the monitoring watchlist\",\n      \"toolClass\": \"destructive\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to stop monitoring\" }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"list_monitors\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists all currently monitored URLs with their latest status and uptime percentage\",\n      \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"status_filter\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Filter by status: 'up', 'down', or 'all' (default: 'all')\" }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"get_uptime_history\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns the check history and uptime statistics for a monitored URL over a given time range\",\n      \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The monitored URL to get history for\" },\n        \"hours\": { \"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Number of hours of history to retrieve (default: 24)\" }\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"prompts\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"uptime_report\",\n      \"description\": \"Generates a summary report of all monitored URLs including uptime percentages, average response times, and any recent incidents\",\n      \"arguments\": [\n        { \"name\": \"period\", \"description\": \"Time period for the report: '24h', '7d', or '30d'\", \"required\": true }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```",
    "status": "done",
    "duration_ms": 12627,
    "cost_usd": 0.06627475000000001,
    "user_id": "usr-2d1a32a2a3c9c373",
    "created_at": "2026-04-15T13:59:58.16336101Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "ses-5bc8503e35f8a89b",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. Generate the JavaScript implementation for each tool below.\n\nIMPORTANT: Respond with ONLY JSON code blocks, one per tool, using ```json:tool markers. No other text.\n\nFor each tool, output:\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"...\",\n  \"params\": { ... },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { ... }\"\n}\n```\n\nThe JS runtime APIs:\n- http.get(url), http.post(url, body), http.put(url, body), http.delete(url) ‚Äî returns {status, body, headers}\n- secrets.get(key), config.get(key) ‚Äî read user settings\n- log.info(msg), log.warn(msg), log.error(msg)\n\nKeep scripts concise and practical. Each must define a handle(params) function.\n\nHere are the tools to implement:\n- check_url: Performs a single health check on a given URL and returns status code, response time, and availability status (class: read-only, params: {\"url\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"The full URL to check (e.g. https://example.com)\"},\"timeout_seconds\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"Request timeout in seconds (default: 10)\"}})\n- add_monitor: Adds a URL to the monitoring watchlist with a specified check interval (class: read-write, params: {\"url\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"The URL to monitor\"},\"label\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"A friendly label for this monitor\"},\"interval_minutes\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"How often to check in minutes (default: 5)\"}})\n- remove_monitor: Removes a URL from the monitoring watchlist (class: destructive, params: {\"url\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"The URL to stop monitoring\"}})\n- list_monitors: Lists all currently monitored URLs with their latest status and uptime percentage (class: read-only, params: {\"status_filter\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"Filter by status: 'up', 'down', or 'all' (default: 'all')\"}})\n- get_uptime_history: Returns the check history and uptime statistics for a monitored URL over a given time range (class: read-only, params: {\"url\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"The monitored URL to get history for\"},\"hours\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"Number of hours of history to retrieve (default: 24)\"}})",
    "result": "\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"check_url\",\n  \"description\": \"Performs a single health check on a given URL and returns status code, response time, and availability status\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The full URL to check (e.g. https://example.com)\"},\n    \"timeout_seconds\": {\"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Request timeout in seconds (default: 10)\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { var timeout = (params.timeout_seconds || 10) * 1000; var start = Date.now(); try { var resp = http.get(params.url); var elapsed = Date.now() - start; var isUp = resp.status \u003e= 200 \u0026\u0026 resp.status \u003c 400; return { url: params.url, status_code: resp.status, response_time_ms: elapsed, available: isUp, status: isUp ? 'up' : 'down', checked_at: new Date().toISOString() }; } catch (e) { var elapsed = Date.now() - start; return { url: params.url, status_code: 0, response_time_ms: elapsed, available: false, status: 'down', error: e.message, checked_at: new Date().toISOString() }; } }\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"add_monitor\",\n  \"description\": \"Adds a URL to the monitoring watchlist with a specified check interval\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-write\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to monitor\"},\n    \"label\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"A friendly label for this monitor\"},\n    \"interval_minutes\": {\"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"How often to check in minutes (default: 5)\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { var key = 'monitors'; var monitors = config.get(key) || {}; if (monitors[params.url]) { return { success: false, message: 'URL is already being monitored', url: params.url }; } monitors[params.url] = { url: params.url, label: params.label || params.url, interval_minutes: params.interval_minutes || 5, added_at: new Date().toISOString(), checks: [], total_checks: 0, up_checks: 0 }; config.set(key, monitors); log.info('Added monitor for ' + params.url); return { success: true, message: 'Monitor added', monitor: monitors[params.url] }; }\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"remove_monitor\",\n  \"description\": \"Removes a URL from the monitoring watchlist\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"destructive\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to stop monitoring\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { var key = 'monitors'; var monitors = config.get(key) || {}; if (!monitors[params.url]) { return { success: false, message: 'URL is not being monitored', url: params.url }; } var removed = monitors[params.url]; delete monitors[params.url]; config.set(key, monitors); log.info('Removed monitor for ' + params.url); return { success: true, message: 'Monitor removed', removed: { url: params.url, label: removed.label } }; }\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"list_monitors\",\n  \"description\": \"Lists all currently monitored URLs with their latest status and uptime percentage\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"status_filter\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Filter by status: 'up', 'down', or 'all' (default: 'all')\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { var filter = params.status_filter || 'all'; var monitors = config.get('monitors') || {}; var results = []; var urls = Object.keys(monitors); for (var i = 0; i \u003c urls.length; i++) { var m = monitors[urls[i]]; var checks = m.checks || []; var lastCheck = checks.length \u003e 0 ? checks[checks.length - 1] : null; var lastStatus = lastCheck ? lastCheck.status : 'unknown'; var uptime = m.total_checks \u003e 0 ? Math.round((m.up_checks / m.total_checks) * 10000) / 100 : 0; if (filter !== 'all' \u0026\u0026 lastStatus !== filter) continue; results.push({ url: m.url, label: m.label, status: lastStatus, uptime_percent: uptime, interval_minutes: m.interval_minutes, total_checks: m.total_checks, last_checked: lastCheck ? lastCheck.checked_at : null }); } return { total: results.length, filter: filter, monitors: results }; }\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"get_uptime_history\",\n  \"description\": \"Returns the check history and uptime statistics for a monitored URL over a given time range\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The monitored URL to get history for\"},\n    \"hours\": {\"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Number of hours of history to retrieve (default: 24)\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { var monitors = config.get('monitors') || {}; var m = monitors[params.url]; if (!m) { return { success: false, message: 'URL is not being monitored', url: params.url }; } var hours = params.hours || 24; var cutoff = new Date(Date.now() - hours * 3600 * 1000).toISOString(); var checks = (m.checks || []).filter(function(c) { return c.checked_at \u003e= cutoff; }); var upCount = 0; var totalTime = 0; for (var i = 0; i \u003c checks.length; i++) { if (checks[i].status === 'up') upCount++; totalTime += checks[i].response_time_ms || 0; } var avgResponse = checks.length \u003e 0 ? Math.round(totalTime / checks.length) : 0; var uptime = checks.length \u003e 0 ? Math.round((upCount / checks.length) * 10000) / 100 : 0; return { url: params.url, label: m.label, period_hours: hours, total_checks: checks.length, up_checks: upCount, down_checks: checks.length - upCount, uptime_percent: uptime, avg_response_time_ms: avgResponse, checks: checks }; }\"\n}\n```",
    "status": "done",
    "duration_ms": 19402,
    "cost_usd": 0.0917215,
    "user_id": "usr-2d1a32a2a3c9c373",
    "created_at": "2026-04-15T14:00:31.6438856Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "ses-86d2434fef8491b8",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. The user is building a store app and needs help creating tools and prompts.\n\nIMPORTANT: When generating a tool, you MUST output a JSON code block with the marker \"json:tool\" like this:\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n  \"description\": \"What the tool does\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"param_name\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"Param description\" }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  const result = http.get('https://example.com/api');\\n  return { data: result };\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\nWhen generating a prompt, use the marker \"json:prompt\":\n\n```json:prompt\n{\n  \"name\": \"prompt_name\",\n  \"description\": \"What the prompt does\",\n  \"body\": \"Markdown template body with {{variable}} placeholders\"\n}\n```\n\nCRITICAL: Always use ```json:tool or ```json:prompt markers, NOT plain ```json.\n\nThe JS runtime has these APIs:\n- http.get(url), http.post(url, body), http.put(url, body), http.delete(url)\n- secrets.get(key), config.get(key)\n- log.info(msg), log.warn(msg), log.error(msg)\n\nHTTP calls are restricted to the app's allowedHosts. The handle(params) function receives the tool's declared params. Keep scripts concise.\n\nTESTING: After the user adds a tool to their app, they can ask you to test it. The app's tools are available via MCP with the naming pattern \"appname.toolname\". You have access to MCP tools ‚Äî call them to test. If a tool needs allowedHosts to make HTTP calls, remind the user to add the domain in the Permissions tab.\n\nThe user's app context:\nApp name: \"test\", Description: \"\"\n\nUser request: Create a tool that checks if a URL is reachable",
    "result": "Here's a tool that checks if a URL is reachable:\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"check_url\",\n  \"description\": \"Checks if a URL is reachable by making an HTTP GET request and returning the status\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"The URL to check (e.g. https://example.com)\" }\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  try {\\n    const resp = http.get(params.url);\\n    return { reachable: true, status: resp.status, url: params.url };\\n  } catch (e) {\\n    return { reachable: false, error: e.message, url: params.url };\\n  }\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\n**How it works:** Makes a GET request to the provided URL. Returns `reachable: true` with the HTTP status code on success, or `reachable: false` with the error message on failure.\n\n**Note:** After adding this tool, make sure to add the domain(s) you want to check in the **Permissions** tab under `allowedHosts` (e.g. `example.com`). HTTP calls are blocked for hosts not on the allow list.\n\nWant me to adjust anything ‚Äî like adding a timeout, checking multiple URLs at once, or returning response time?",
