  {
    "id": "ses-7590d3ddeff8c79a",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI app builder for NubeIO. Generate the JavaScript implementation for each tool below.\n\nIMPORTANT: Respond with ONLY JSON code blocks, one per tool, using ```json:tool markers. No other text.\n\nFor each tool, output:\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"tool_name\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"...\",\n  \"params\": { ... },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) { ... }\"\n}\n```\n\nThe JS runtime APIs:\n- http.get(url), http.post(url, body), http.put(url, body), http.delete(url) ‚Äî returns {status, body, headers}\n- secrets.get(key), config.get(key) ‚Äî read user settings\n- log.info(msg), log.warn(msg), log.error(msg)\n\nKeep scripts concise and practical. Each must define a handle(params) function.\n\nHere are the tools to implement:\n- get_current_weather: Get current weather conditions for a specific city including temperature, humidity, wind speed, and conditions (class: read-only, params: {\"city\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"City name to get weather for\"},\"units\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"Temperature units: metric or imperial (default: metric)\"}})\n- get_forecast: Get a multi-day weather forecast for a specific city (class: read-only, params: {\"city\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"City name to get the forecast for\"},\"days\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"Number of forecast days (1-7, default: 5)\"}})\n- compare_cities: Compare current weather conditions across multiple cities side by side (class: read-only, params: {\"cities\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"Comma-separated list of city names to compare\"},\"units\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":\"Temperature units: metric or imperial (default: metric)\"}})\n- get_weather_alerts: Check for active weather alerts and warnings for a specific city or region (class: read-only, params: {\"city\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":\"City name to check alerts for\"}})",
    "result": "\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"get_current_weather\",\n  \"description\": \"Get current weather conditions for a specific city including temperature, humidity, wind speed, and conditions\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"city\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"City name to get weather for\"},\n    \"units\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Temperature units: metric or imperial (default: metric)\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  var apiKey = secrets.get('OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY');\\n  if (!apiKey) { return {error: 'Missing OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY secret'}; }\\n  var units = params.units || 'metric';\\n  var url = 'https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=' + encodeURIComponent(params.city) + '\u0026units=' + units + '\u0026appid=' + apiKey;\\n  var resp = http.get(url);\\n  if (resp.status !== 200) { return {error: 'Failed to fetch weather', status: resp.status, detail: resp.body}; }\\n  var d = resp.body;\\n  var tempUnit = units === 'imperial' ? '¬∞F' : '¬∞C';\\n  var speedUnit = units === 'imperial' ? 'mph' : 'm/s';\\n  return {\\n    city: d.name,\\n    country: d.sys.country,\\n    temperature: d.main.temp + tempUnit,\\n    feels_like: d.main.feels_like + tempUnit,\\n    humidity: d.main.humidity + '%',\\n    wind_speed: d.wind.speed + speedUnit,\\n    conditions: d.weather[0].description,\\n    icon: d.weather[0].icon\\n  };\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"get_forecast\",\n  \"description\": \"Get a multi-day weather forecast for a specific city\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"city\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"City name to get the forecast for\"},\n    \"days\": {\"type\": \"number\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Number of forecast days (1-7, default: 5)\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  var apiKey = secrets.get('OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY');\\n  if (!apiKey) { return {error: 'Missing OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY secret'}; }\\n  var days = params.days || 5;\\n  if (days \u003c 1) days = 1;\\n  if (days \u003e 7) days = 7;\\n  var url = 'https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/forecast?q=' + encodeURIComponent(params.city) + '\u0026units=metric\u0026cnt=' + (days * 8) + '\u0026appid=' + apiKey;\\n  var resp = http.get(url);\\n  if (resp.status !== 200) { return {error: 'Failed to fetch forecast', status: resp.status, detail: resp.body}; }\\n  var d = resp.body;\\n  var dailyMap = {};\\n  for (var i = 0; i \u003c d.list.length; i++) {\\n    var item = d.list[i];\\n    var date = item.dt_txt.split(' ')[0];\\n    if (!dailyMap[date]) {\\n      dailyMap[date] = {date: date, temp_min: item.main.temp_min, temp_max: item.main.temp_max, conditions: item.weather[0].description, humidity: item.main.humidity};\\n    } else {\\n      if (item.main.temp_min \u003c dailyMap[date].temp_min) dailyMap[date].temp_min = item.main.temp_min;\\n      if (item.main.temp_max \u003e dailyMap[date].temp_max) dailyMap[date].temp_max = item.main.temp_max;\\n    }\\n  }\\n  var forecast = [];\\n  for (var key in dailyMap) { forecast.push(dailyMap[key]); }\\n  forecast.sort(function(a, b) { return a.date.localeCompare(b.date); });\\n  return {city: d.city.name, country: d.city.country, days: days, forecast: forecast.slice(0, days)};\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"compare_cities\",\n  \"description\": \"Compare current weather conditions across multiple cities side by side\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"cities\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"Comma-separated list of city names to compare\"},\n    \"units\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": false, \"description\": \"Temperature units: metric or imperial (default: metric)\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  var apiKey = secrets.get('OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY');\\n  if (!apiKey) { return {error: 'Missing OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY secret'}; }\\n  var units = params.units || 'metric';\\n  var tempUnit = units === 'imperial' ? '¬∞F' : '¬∞C';\\n  var speedUnit = units === 'imperial' ? 'mph' : 'm/s';\\n  var cityList = params.cities.split(',').map(function(c) { return c.trim(); }).filter(function(c) { return c.length \u003e 0; });\\n  if (cityList.length === 0) { return {error: 'No cities provided'}; }\\n  var results = [];\\n  for (var i = 0; i \u003c cityList.length; i++) {\\n    var url = 'https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=' + encodeURIComponent(cityList[i]) + '\u0026units=' + units + '\u0026appid=' + apiKey;\\n    var resp = http.get(url);\\n    if (resp.status !== 200) {\\n      results.push({city: cityList[i], error: 'Failed to fetch', status: resp.status});\\n    } else {\\n      var d = resp.body;\\n      results.push({city: d.name, country: d.sys.country, temperature: d.main.temp + tempUnit, feels_like: d.main.feels_like + tempUnit, humidity: d.main.humidity + '%', wind_speed: d.wind.speed + speedUnit, conditions: d.weather[0].description});\\n    }\\n  }\\n  return {units: units, comparison: results};\\n}\"\n}\n```\n\n```json:tool\n{\n  \"name\": \"get_weather_alerts\",\n  \"description\": \"Check for active weather alerts and warnings for a specific city or region\",\n  \"toolClass\": \"read-only\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"city\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"required\": true, \"description\": \"City name to check alerts for\"}\n  },\n  \"script\": \"function handle(params) {\\n  var apiKey = secrets.get('OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY');\\n  if (!apiKey) { return {error: 'Missing OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY secret'}; }\\n  var geoUrl = 'https://api.openweathermap.org/geo/1.0/direct?q=' + encodeURIComponent(params.city) + '\u0026limit=1\u0026appid=' + apiKey;\\n  var geoResp = http.get(geoUrl);\\n  if (geoResp.status !== 200 || !geoResp.body || geoResp.body.length === 0) {\\n    return {error: 'Could not geocode city', city: params.city};\\n  }\\n  var lat = geoResp.body[0].lat;\\n  var lon = geoResp.body[0].lon;\\n  var url = 'https://api.openweathermap.org/data/3.0/onecall?lat=' + lat + '\u0026lon=' + lon + '\u0026exclude=minutely,hourly,daily\u0026appid=' + apiKey;\\n  var resp = http.get(url);\\n  if (resp.status !== 200) { return {error: 'Failed to fetch alerts', status: resp.status, detail: resp.body}; }\\n  var d = resp.body;\\n  var alerts = d.alerts || [];\\n  var formatted = alerts.map(function(a) {\\n    return {event: a.event, sender: a.sender_name, start: a.start, end: a.end, description: a.description};\\n  });\\n  return {city: params.city, lat: lat, lon: lon, alert_count: formatted.length, alerts: formatted};\\n}\"\n}\n```",
