  {
    "id": "ses-f19a39dc9e51cc93",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are helping the user query nodes in Rubix using the Haystack filter language.\n\nThe user wants to find: all\n\n## How to Query\n\nCall `rubix.query_filter` with orgId, deviceId, and a `filter` string using Haystack syntax.\n\n## Haystack Filter Syntax\n\n**By type:**\n- `type is \"core.trigger\"` ‚Äî exact type match\n- `type in [\"core.trigger\", \"core.counter\"]` ‚Äî multiple types\n\n**By name:**\n- `name contains \"Supply\"` ‚Äî substring match\n- `name like \"valve%\"` ‚Äî wildcard\n\n**By identity tags (fast):**\n- `i has \"sensor\"` ‚Äî has tag\n- `i has [\"temp\", \"humid\"]` ‚Äî has any of these tags\n- `i hasAll [\"temp\", \"sensor\", \"point\"]` ‚Äî has all tags\n\n**By refs:**\n- `siteRef is \"node_001\"` ‚Äî at a specific site\n- `equipRef is \"ahu_01\"` ‚Äî belongs to equipment\n- `parentRef is \"dev_123\"` ‚Äî direct children\n\n**By port values:**\n- `out.valueNum \u003e 20` ‚Äî output value above 20\n- `state.value is \"active\"` ‚Äî string port value\n\n**By alarm state:**\n- `i has \"alarm\" and state.value is \"active\"` ‚Äî active alarms\n- `severity.value is \"Critical\"` ‚Äî critical alarms\n\n**By settings (JSONB):**\n- `settings.productCode contains \"widget\"` ‚Äî settings field search\n\n**Combining:**\n- `type is \"sensor\" and name contains \"Temp\"` ‚Äî AND\n- `i has \"temp\" or i has \"humid\"` ‚Äî OR\n- `not (status is \"inactive\")` ‚Äî NOT\n- `(i has \"temp\" or i has \"humid\") and siteRef is \"site_1\"` ‚Äî grouping\n\n**Modifiers (pipe):**\n- `type is \"device\" | limit 50` ‚Äî limit results\n- `type is \"device\" | sort name asc` ‚Äî sort\n- `type is \"device\" | offset 10 | limit 10` ‚Äî pagination\n- `type is \"trigger\" | select out, in1` ‚Äî port projection\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Translate the user's natural language request into a Haystack filter\n2. Call `rubix.query_filter` with the filter\n3. Present the results in a clear table or list\n4. If no results, suggest alternative filters",
    "result": "\n\nI need an `orgId` and `deviceId` to run the query. Do you have these, or should I look them up first?",
