    "id": "ses-d8b92d4b38404deb",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI assistant for the \"rubix\" app (rubix). Rubix Building Automation ‚Äî query nodes, build flows, analyze history, create dashboards\n\nThe app has these tools: none.\nAnd these prompts: rubix.build_dashboard ‚Äî Create dashboard pages with widgets, templates, and data queries for the Rubix scene builder; rubix.create_flow ‚Äî Create nodes and connect them with edges to build automation flows; rubix.getting_started ‚Äî Get started with Rubix ‚Äî login, discover the system, understand the node hierarchy; rubix.history_analysis ‚Äî Query and analyze historical time-series data from Rubix nodes; rubix.navigation ‚Äî Build site navigation hierarchy ‚Äî sites, buildings, floors with containers and nav links; rubix.query_nodes ‚Äî Query nodes using the Rubix Haystack filter language; rubix.tagging ‚Äî Manage tags and identity markers on Rubix nodes for classification and fast querying.\n\nUse the app's tools to help the user. Prefer the JS tools (rubix.*) over generic OpenAPI tools when available.\n\nUser: /rubix.getting_started",
    "result": "Let me get started with Rubix! First, let me check the API info and available auth tools.# Getting Started with Rubix\n\nRubix is a **Building Automation** platform that lets you query nodes, build flows, analyze history, and create dashboards.\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Authentication\n\nYou need to log in first. Rubix supports two login methods:\n\n| Method | When to use |\n|--------|------------|\n| **PIN Login** (recommended) | Log in with your Org ID + 6-digit PIN |\n| **Email/Password** | Log in with email and password |\n\n**To log in, provide one of the following:**\n\n- **PIN Login**: Your `orgId` and 6-digit `pin`\n- **Email Login**: Your `email` and `password`\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Discover the System\n\nOnce authenticated, you can explore using these available prompts:\n\n| Prompt | Description |\n|--------|------------|\n| `/rubix.navigation` | Build site navigation ‚Äî sites, buildings, floors |\n| `/rubix.query_nodes` | Query nodes using the Rubix Haystack filter language |\n| `/rubix.create_flow` | Create nodes and connect them with edges for automation |\n| `/rubix.history_analysis` | Query and analyze historical time-series data |\n| `/rubix.build_dashboard` | Create dashboard pages with widgets and templates |\n| `/rubix.tagging` | Manage tags and identity markers on nodes |\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Understand the Node Hierarchy\n\nRubix organizes everything as **nodes** in a hierarchy:\n\n```\nOrg ‚Üí Site ‚Üí Building ‚Üí Floor ‚Üí Equipment ‚Üí Points\n```\n\nYou can query, tag, and automate across this structure.\n\n---\n\n## Ready to begin?\n\nPlease provide your login credentials to get started:\n- **PIN login**: Give me your Org ID and 6-digit PIN\n- **Email login**: Give me your email and password\n\nOnce logged in, I can help you explore your system, query nodes, build flows, or create dashboards.",
