    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are an AI assistant for the \"rubix\" app (rubix). Rubix Building Automation ‚Äî query nodes, build flows, analyze history, create dashboards\n\nThe app has these tools: none.\nAnd these prompts: rubix.build_dashboard ‚Äî Create dashboard pages with widgets, templates, and data queries for the Rubix scene builder; rubix.create_flow ‚Äî Create nodes and connect them with edges to build automation flows; rubix.getting_started ‚Äî Get started with Rubix ‚Äî login, discover the system, understand the node hierarchy; rubix.history_analysis ‚Äî Query and analyze historical time-series data from Rubix nodes; rubix.navigation ‚Äî Build site navigation hierarchy ‚Äî sites, buildings, floors with containers and nav links; rubix.query_nodes ‚Äî Query nodes using the Rubix Haystack filter language; rubix.tagging ‚Äî Manage tags and identity markers on Rubix nodes for classification and fast querying.\n\nUse the app's tools to help the user. Prefer the JS tools (rubix.*) over generic OpenAPI tools when available.\n\nUser: /rubix.getting_started",
    "result": "Let me help you get started with Rubix. I'll load the necessary tools to check your connection and discover the system.Let me check your connection and system status.Great, you're connected and authenticated. Here's your Rubix system overview:\n\n---\n\n## Rubix ‚Äî Getting Started\n\n### Connection Status\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **API** | Rubix API v1.0.0 |\n| **Status** | Running |\n| **Uptime** | ~1h 7m |\n\n### Your Account\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Email** | admin@rubix.io |\n| **Role** | org-admin |\n| **Org ID** | test |\n| **Team ID** | tem_AF7863D2164E |\n| **PIN Login** | Enabled |\n\n### Runtime\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Device ID** | dev_01A12A00AB0C |\n| **Nodes** | 68 |\n| **Edges** | 0 |\n\n---\n\n### What you can do next\n\n1. **Query nodes** ‚Äî Search and filter your 68 nodes using the Rubix query language (e.g. by tags, references, type)\n2. **Create flows** ‚Äî Build automation logic by creating nodes and connecting them with edges\n3. **Analyze history** ‚Äî Query time-series data from your nodes for trends and diagnostics\n4. **Build dashboards** ‚Äî Create pages with widgets and templates to visualize your data\n5. **Manage navigation** ‚Äî Set up your site hierarchy (sites, buildings, floors)\n6. **Tag nodes** ‚Äî Classify nodes with identity tags for fast querying\n\nWould you like to explore any of these? For example, I can list your nodes, show available node types, or help you build a flow.",
