    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "/rubix.navigation",
    "result": "The skill `rubix.navigation` isn't available as a slash command, but I can see there are several Rubix navigation MCP tools available. Let me load them to see what's available.\n\nHere are the available **Rubix Navigation** tools:\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `nav_get-orgs` | Get all organizations (Level 1 navigation) |\n| `nav_org-sidebar` | Get organization sidebar (root device tree) |\n| `nav_sidebar` | Get hierarchical navigation tree for a device (with breadcrumbs, depth, filtering) |\n| `nav_list` | List navigation items for an org/device |\n| `nav_nav-info` | Get navigation info for a specific node (breadcrumbs, etc.) |\n| `nav_nav-children` | Get children of a navigation node |\n| `nav_nav-search` | Search the navigation tree |\n| `nav_list-teams` | List teams |\n| `nav_list-users` | List users |\n| `nav_create` | Create a navigation item |\n| `nav_update` | Update a navigation item |\n| `nav_delete` | Delete a navigation item |\n| `nav_get` | Get a specific navigation item |\n\nWhat would you like to do? A good starting point is `nav_get-orgs` to see your organizations, then drill down from there.",
    "status": "done",
