    "id": "ses-c7aba57386e3d932",
    "provider": "claude",
    "prompt": "You are a helpful AI assistant with access to the user's installed apps, tools, and prompts via MCP. Help them accomplish tasks using the available tools.\n\nYou are helping the user manage the Rubix navigation hierarchy.\n\nThe user wants to: {{action}}\n\n## IMPORTANT: Auth is automatic. NEVER ask for orgId or deviceId. The login gives you both.\n\n## Step 1: Show what exists\n\nFirst call `rubix.runtime_status` (no params needed) to get the system context.\n\nThen call `rubix.query_nodes` with filter `type is \"ui.container\"` to see all existing navigation containers.\n\nPresent the results as a tree. Look at parentId to determine hierarchy:\n```\nSite: Sydney Office (id: xxx)\n  Building: Tower A (id: yyy)\n    Floor: Level 1 (id: zzz)\n    Floor: Level 2 (id: aaa)\n```\n\n## If user wants to CREATE new navigation\n\nUse `rubix.create_node` for each level. It handles auth and parentRef automatically.\n\n**Site (top level, no parentName needed):**\n```json\n{\"type\": \"ui.container\", \"name\": \"Sydney Office\", \"tags\": \"site\", \"settings\": \"{\\\"containerType\\\": \\\"site\\\"}\"}\n```\n\n**Building (under a site ‚Äî use parentName):**\n```json\n{\"type\": \"ui.container\", \"name\": \"Tower A\", \"parentName\": \"Sydney Office\", \"tags\": \"building\"}\n```\n\n**Floor (under a building):**\n```json\n{\"type\": \"ui.container\", \"name\": \"Level 1\", \"parentName\": \"Tower A\", \"tags\": \"floor\"}\n```\n\nCreate top-down: site first, then buildings, then floors. Each `create_node` returns the new node's ID.\n\n## If user wants to EDIT existing\n\nUse `rubix.get_node` with the node name to find it, then `rubix.update_node` to change it:\n- Rename: `{\"name\": \"Floor 1\", \"newName\": \"Ground Floor\"}`\n- Move: `{\"name\": \"Level 1\", \"settings\": \"{\\\"containerType\\\": \\\"zone\\\"}\"}`\n\nUse `rubix.delete_node` to remove (cascades to children).\n\n## If user just wants to SEE navigation\n\nCall `rubix.query_nodes` with these filters:\n- All sites: `i has \"site\"`\n- All buildings: `i has \"building\"`\n- All floors: `i has \"floor\"`\n- Everything: `type is \"ui.container\"`\n\nPresent as a clear hierarchy tree.",
    "result": "Let me start by checking the current system status and existing navigation containers.The system is running (62 nodes, 0 edges), but the query hit an auth token conflict. Let me retry the query.Here's the current navigation hierarchy:\n\n```\nDrivers\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Hardware Drivers   (id: ...-hardware-drivers-folder)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Protocol Drivers   (id: ...-protocol-drivers-folder)\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Rubix Networks     (id: ...-rubix-networks-folder)\n\nServices\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Automation         (id: ...-automation-folder)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Monitoring         (id: ...-monitoring-folder)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Data               (id: ...-data-folder)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Graphics           (id: ...-graphics-folder)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ System             (id: ...-system-folder)\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Extensions         (id: ...-extensions-folder)\n```\n\nThere are **9 containers** organized under two parent groups: **Drivers** (3) and **Services** (6). Currently there are no site/building/floor navigation nodes ‚Äî these are all system-level containers.\n\nWhat would you like to do? For example:\n- **Create** a site/building/floor hierarchy (e.g. \"Create site Sydney Office with buildings Tower A and Tower B\")\n- **Rename** or **move** an existing container\n- **Delete** a container\n- **Add** new containers under an existing group",
    "status": "done",
    "duration_ms": 21577,
    "cost_usd": 0.0988125,
    "user_id": "usr-2d1a32a2a3c9c373",
    "created_at": "2026-04-16T06:21:28.689352769Z"
  },
